signs.(-1, 2) - (14, 9): Gems are optional rewards, and can be very hard! If you can't get one, consider moving on and coming back later.
signs.(-2, 2) - (13, 12): You can always undo and redo moves, restart a level from the pause menu, and sometimes the solution involves resetting. Don't be afraid to experiment!
signs.(-2, 2) - (10, 8): If you're ever stuck in a level, you can always use the map to teleport back to a level that contains a teleporter, like this one!
signs.(-7, 3) - (8, 11): The following puzzles are extremely difficult.
signs.(-7, 3) - (8, 12): They use a wide variety of techniques and objects, including some you might not know about yet.
signs.(-7, 3) - (8, 13): If you don't want to solve these, use the map to teleport to a different level.
signs.(-1, -5) - (1, 9): For example, you can step back on to the portal and use it to skip to the end of this area. Or you can use undo!
signs.(-1, -6) - (9, 2): This is a portal! Once activated, you can use them to skip back and forth through sections of levels.
signs.(-1, -7) - (9, 12): Welcome to the second world! This world is a lot bigger than the first, so here's some advice for you...
signs.(-1, -7) - (10, 11): These levels can be tackled in any order, and the first ones you find won't necessarily be the easiest! If you're stuck, consider switching to a different level.
signs.(-1, -7) - (10, 10): Remember, gems are optional and can be very, very, VERY hard to collect. If you can't get a gem (or figure out a secret) consider coming back later.
signs.(-1, -7) - (10, 9): Also, don't forget you can undo and redo moves, teleport via the map or activated portals, and restart levels from the pause menu.
signs.(-1, -7) - (10, 8): Lastly, have fun exploring and good luck!
